+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q4V1fAKwMJLL7SBv2J4gCA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Project Structure Exploration - Complete Report\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the `/workspace` project. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. PROJECT OVERVIEW\n\n**Project Name:** `bench-collab-server` (Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor)\n**Type:** Greenfield/Complex TypeScript project\n**Timeout:** 30 minutes\n**Current State:** Empty source code (no implementation yet)\n\n### 2. FILE STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                 (ESLint configuration)\n├── .gitignore                    (Git ignore rules)\n├── .thunderdome/\n│   └── rubric.yaml              (Scoring rubric for automated testing)\n├── TASK.md                       (High-level requirements/description)\n├── package.json                  (NPM project manifest)\n├── package-lock.json             (Locked dependency versions)\n├── tsconfig.json                 (TypeScript configuration)\n├── vitest.config.ts              (Test runner configuration)\n├── schema.sql                    (SQLite database schema)\n├── src/\n│   └── .gitkeep                  (Empty - no source files yet)\n├── .thunderdome-output.jsonl     (Test output from last run)\n└── .thunderdome-stderr.log       (Error log from last run)\n```\n\n### 3. PACKAGE.JSON DEPENDENCIES\n\n**Production Dependencies:**\n- `ws@^8.18.0` - WebSocket library for real-time communication\n- `better-sqlite3@^11.0.0` - SQLite database driver\n- `express@^4.21.0` - HTTP server framework\n\n**Development Dependencies:**\n- `typescript@^5.4.0` - TypeScript compiler\n- `vitest@^2.0.0` - Test framework\n- `@vitest/coverage-v8@^2.0.0` - Code coverage\n- `eslint@^8.56.0` - Linter\n- `@typescript-eslint/parser@^7.0.0` - TypeScript ESLint parser\n- `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin@^7.0.0` - TypeScript ESLint rules\n- `@types/ws@^8.5.0` - Type definitions for WebSocket\n- `@types/better-sqlite3@^7.6.0` - Type definitions for SQLite\n- `@types/express@^4.17.0` - Type definitions for Express\n- `supertest@^7.0.0` - HTTP testing library\n- `@types/supertest@^6.0.0` - Type definitions for supertest\n\n### 4. BUILD/LINT/TEST CONFIGURATION\n\n**TypeScript (tsconfig.json):**\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16\n- Strict mode: enabled\n- Output: `./dist`\n- Root: `./src`\n- Include: `src/**/*`\n- Exclude: `node_modules`, `dist`, `tests`\n- Features: Source maps, declaration files, declaration maps\n\n**ESLint (.eslintrc.cjs):**\n- Parser: @typescript-eslint/parser\n- Extends: eslint:recommended + plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended\n- ECMAVersion: 2022\n- Environment: Node.js, ES2022\n- Rules: No unused variables (except those starting with `_`)\n\n**Vitest (vitest.config.ts):**\n- Global test utilities: enabled\n- Test timeout: 10 seconds\n\n**NPM Scripts (package.json):**\n- `npm run build` → `tsc` (TypeScript compilation)\n- `npm run lint` → `eslint src/` (Linting)\n- `npm run test` → `vitest run` (Test execution)\n\n### 5. DATABASE SCHEMA (schema.sql)\n\nThree tables defined:\n\n1. **documents** - Main document storage\n   - `id` (TEXT PRIMARY KEY) - Document identifier\n   - `title` (TEXT NOT NULL) - Document title\n   - `content` (TEXT, default: '') - Document content\n   - `created_at` (TEXT, default: now)\n   - `updated_at` (TEXT, default: now)\n\n2. **versions** - Version history tracking\n   - `id` (INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT)\n   - `document_id` (TEXT FOREIGN KEY) - Reference to documents\n   - `version` (INTEGER) - Version number\n   - `content` (TEXT) - Document content at this version\n   - `operation` (TEXT) - JSON representation of the operation\n   - `created_at` (TEXT, default: now)\n   - UNIQUE constraint on (document_id, version)\n\n3. **active_connections** - Real-time connection tracking\n   - `id` (TEXT PRIMARY KEY)\n   - `document_id` (TEXT FOREIGN KEY)\n   - `connected_at` (TEXT, default: now)\n\n### 6. REQUIREMENTS (from TASK.md)\n\nThe project needs to implement a collaborative real-time document editor server with:\n\n1. **REST API for document management** (CRUD operations)\n   - Create, read, update, list, delete documents\n   - Version history endpoint\n\n2. **WebSocket-based real-time collaboration**\n   - Connect clients via WebSocket with document ID\n   - Send current state on connection\n   - Broadcast edits to other connected users\n\n3. **Conflict resolution**\n   - Implement Operational Transform (OT) or CRDTs\n   - Ensure concurrent edits don't corrupt document\n   - All changes must be preserved\n\n4. **Persistence**\n   - SQLite via better-sqlite3\n   - Data survives server restarts\n\n5. **Robustness**\n   - Handle 10+ concurrent clients\n   - Graceful error handling\n   - No crashes from malformed input\n\n6. **Structural requirement**\n   - Export `createApp` factory function from `src/server.ts` or `src/index.ts`\n   - Returns object with: `app`, `start(port?)`, `stop()`\n\n### 7. SCORING RUBRIC (.thunderdome/rubric.yaml)\n\n100-point scale, 70-point pass threshold:\n\n- **Build** (10 pts) - TypeScript compilation\n- **Lint** (5 pts) - ESLint pass\n- **REST CRUD** (15 pts) - 10 tests for document operations\n- **WebSocket Lifecycle** (15 pts) - 8 tests for connection management\n- **Single Client Editing** (10 pts) - 6 tests for basic operations\n- **Two-Client Convergence** (20 pts) - 8 tests for OT conflict resolution\n- **Stress Test** (15 pts) - 5 tests for 10 concurrent clients\n- **Error Handling** (5 pts) - 5 tests for malformed input gracefully\n- **Persistence** (5 pts) - 3 tests for data survival across restarts\n\n**Total test count:** 45 tests across 7 categories\n\n### 8. GIT HISTORY\n\n- **Commit 2dc69c3** (Most recent) - \"greenfield: remove tests, rewrite TASK.md as vague requirements\"\n  - Removed: `tests/collab.test.ts`\n  - Modified: `TASK.md`